title: Shared Ride? Do not believe Uber’s time estimate
text:
I decided to try the shared Ride service. For what would have been a 15-17 minute direct ride, Uber predicted the share would add 6 minutes. 

What actually happened was driving miles out of the way and, taking an additional 20 minutes, and dropping me more than 15 minutes after their “latest drop-off time.”

I am not likely to believe them about that again.

title: UBER SCAMS YOUR RIDES
text: I’ve been an UberOne member for 2 years now and never been so upset. First off they continuously scam you by having it auto select for XL Ubers. I’ve manually had to keep changing this and got screwed 3 times by it. Then they changed my fee and charged me $54 for a ride that was supposed to be $20 when I booked. Guess why? They changed it to XL. As a military member I’m on a very fixed income and this has stolen money from me so many times. I’ve tried contacting them but there’s has been no real person to speak with. Highly recommend switching to a different service that doesn’t continuously try to rob their customers. Absolutely despicable.
